Hi,

On Thursday 15 February 2001 04:55, Shane Ponting wrote:
> > Btw, this brings back to mind that nobody has yet volunteered to carry on
> > with the Virge driver. Anybody ?
>
> Virge is both the CV3D & the Mediator Virge isn't it ? (I was just wanting
> to know)

Theoretically yes. The problem is that the Virge boards for Mediator use 
CXG3. It's not possible to do a decent graphics memory allocation under CGX3, 
as there's no bitmap cache. The old CV3D just had a one megabyte memory area 
on top of it's ram for textures (the MULTIMEDIAMEM area), and the ZBuffer was 
just put in front of that (finger crossed it's not overwritten by a screen). 
So a decent Mediator Virge driver would have to ensure that no texture is 
being overwritten by screen bitmaps, plus the memory allocation would have to 
be done by the driver itself. This is next to impossible, therefore I don't 
think the Mediator Virge boards will ever get a good (and fast) Warp3D 
support.

Regards,
