On Monday 19 February 2001 18:18, Oliver Gantert wrote:
> How much will StormMesa benefit? Wouldn't it be possible to use some
> of the new features of W3D (like vertex arrays) directly from SM?
> I have all SM sources here and am ready to start!

Basically, yes. You could directly map OpenGL array functions to Warp3D V4, 
however, the meaning of the Vertex coordinates is a bit different.

In Warp3D, you have x/y/z as pure flat-geometric coordinates. In OpenGL, you 
have x/y/z/w as 3D coordinates. A intermediate step would be required that 
transforms the x/y/z/w to x/y/z in Warp3D coordinates. However, you could 
then draw all triangles at one go. I do have a test program that paints 25000 
(!) triangles with a single call :-)

Real-Time of course. Well, almost :-) 5000-10000 is still quite smooth, 
though. 

